  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Double Standard Rooms </strong>are around 20m², sleep two people and have one double bed. The rooms have either a balcony or terrace with views over the resort. Interconnecting standard twin rooms are available on request. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Triple Mont Blanc Rooms</strong> are around 28m², sleeping two to three people. They have either one double bed and one single bed or three single beds (please specify when booking) and a balcony with Mont Blanc views.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Summit Rooms</strong> are 20m² and sleep two people. The rooms have air conditioning, safe and a balcony with views of Mont Blanc and Chamonix. </p>
<p><strong>Double Summit R</strong><strong>ooms</strong> are slightly smaller than the twin rooms at 17m² and sleep two people on a double bed. These rooms have a balcony with views of the surrounding mountains and the resort. </p>
<p>Sole occupancy Mountain Double Rooms are available on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book this room type.</p>
<p><strong>Bedroom facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Most rooms have a balcony with resort views</li>
<li>Satellite TV </li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Shower and WC</li>
<li>Kettles (on request)</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
